.SH "NAME"
odgi_explode \- breaks a graph into connected components in their own files
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.sp
\fBodgi explode\fP [\fB\-i, \-\-idx\fP=\fIFILE\fP] [\fB\-p, \-\-prefix\fP=\fISTRING\fP] [\fIOPTION\fP]...
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.sp
The odgi explode(1) command breaks a graph into connected components, writing each component in its own file.
.SH "OPTIONS"
.SS "Graph Files IO"
.sp
\fB\-i, \-\-idx\fP=\fIFILE\fP
.RS 4
File containing the succinct variation graph to break in its components. The file name usually ends with \fI.og\fP.
.RE
.SS "Explode Options"
.sp
\fB\-p, \-\-prefix\fP=\fISTRING\fP
.RS 4
  Write each connected component in a file with the given prefix. The file for the component \f(CRi\fP will be named
\f(CRSTRING.i.og\fP (default: \f(CRcomponent\fP)
.RE
.sp
\fB\-O, \-\-optimize\fP
.RS 4
Compact the node ID space in each connected component.
.RE
.SS "Threading"
.sp
\fB\-t, \-\-threads\fP=\fIN\fP
.RS 4
Number of threads to use (to write the components in parallel).
.RE
.SS "Processing Information"
.sp
\fB\-P, \-\-progress\fP
.RS 4
Print information about the components and the progress to stderr.
.RE
.SS "Program Information"
.sp
\fB\-h, \-\-help\fP
.RS 4
Print a help message for \fBodgi explode\fP.
.RE
.SH "EXIT STATUS"
.sp
\fB0\fP
.RS 4
Success.
.RE
.sp
\fB1\fP
.RS 4
Failure (syntax or usage error; parameter error; file processing failure; unexpected error).
.RE
